The Herald Entertainment Reporter
Former radio presenter Dennis Wilson has died. He was 66. Wilson, born Delroy Wilson in Kingston Jamaica died at his home in Alexandra after a short illness. Wilson became popular on Radio 3 (now Power FM) in the 1990s after landing in the country in the ’80s before being spotted while playing at parties. He joined radio and became an instant hit as a DJ, becoming popular through his signature tune, Freddie McGregor’s Push Comes to Shove. More to follow…